text: Miranda waited, then said, “But what will I do for a whole year?”
Lily stretched her legs out in front of her and cricked her neck. “Oh yes? What do you remember, my Miranda?”
“Indeed. Junior reporter at The Dover Post. Probably just retyping memos from the council on their new initiatives or something. What’s the mannequin for?”
“Er . . . well, then the woman took Eden’s hand and they went home together.”
“Why don’t you think it’s possible?” she asked. “Because everyone can see me?”
“I’m sorry,” Sade said, eyeing me. “You are a maid of Kent, are you not?”
